      "span_text": "The potassium-rich buffer contained 110 mM KCl, 20 mM NaCl, and a 20 mM buffer selected to control pH. 2-(N-morpholino)ethanesulfonic acid (MES; pKa ϭ 6.1) was used to set pH in the range 6.0-6.5; piperazine-N,NЈ-bis(2-ethanesulfonic acid) (PIPES; pKa ϭ 6.8) was used to set pH at 7.0; N-2-hydroxyethylpiperazine-NЈ-2-ethanesulfonic acid (HEPES; pKa ϭ 7.5) was used to set pH at 7.4; and N-tris(hydroxymethyl)methyl-3-aminopropanesulfonic acid (TAPS; pKa ϭ 8.4) was used to set pH at 8."
